# History
This bug was introduced in commit 1890089 (@sudie-codes, 2026-03-18, PR #49583). The commit "fix: serialize duplicate channel starts" refactored the channel startup to prevent duplicate concurrent starts by adding a `startGate` promise. As part of this refactoring, the `manuallyStopped.delete(rKey)` call was moved from BEFORE `isConfigured` to AFTER it. This ordering change meant that if `isConfigured` throws (e.g., network errors in zalouser/whatsapp), the `manuallyStopped` flag remains set, blocking all future recovery attempts until gateway restart.

