This bug was introduced in commit 94693f7 (@gumadeiras, 2026-03-19). The commit was a large-scale Matrix plugin migration that replaced `access-policy.ts` with a new `access-state.ts` module. The original code correctly conditioned `storeAllowFrom` (DM pairing-store approvals) on `isDirectMessage` to prevent DM approvals from authorizing room commands. The refactoring accidentally removed this conditional check, unconditionally merging `storeAllowFrom` into `effectiveAllowFrom` which feeds command authorization for both DM and room traffic. This regressed an explicit security fix from commit 64de4b6d6a which had added the conditional logic to enforce group auth boundaries.

