    - "discord:admin-user-123"

channels:
  discord: {}
  telegram: {}
```
If a heartbeat/cron/exec-triggered session (or any other context where provider cannot be determined) executes with `SenderId: "admin-user-123"`, authorization treats the sender as an owner even though the owner entry is Discord-scoped.

# Recommended Fix
In `resolveOwnerAllowFromList`, reject provider-prefixed entries when the provider is unknown by changing:
```ts
if (params.providerId && channel !== params.providerId) {
```
to:
```ts
if (!params.providerId || channel !== params.providerId) {
```

