This bug was introduced in commit 392bbddf29. The commit added the `resolveOwnerAllowFromList` function to support provider-prefixed owner allowlist entries, but the condition `if (params.providerId && channel !== params.providerId)` only checked the mismatch case when a provider was defined. When `providerId` is undefined (as happens for system events like heartbeat, cron-event, or exec-event), the condition evaluated to false and incorrectly allowed channel-prefixed entries to pass through without the provider-scoping check.

