# Recommended Fix
```typescript
// Add import at top of file:
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "../../routing/session-key.js";

const bindingAccountId = normalizeOptionalString(binding.match.accountId) ?? "";
const isWildcard = bindingAccountId === "*";
if (isWildcard) {
  // Wildcard matches any account with lower priority
} else if (bindingAccountId) {
  const bindingAccountIdNormalized = normalizeAccountId(bindingAccountId);
  if (bindingAccountIdNormalized !== params.accountId) {
    continue;
  }
} else {
  // No accountId specified - only matches default account
  if (params.accountId !== DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID) {
    continue;
  }
}
```

# History
This bug was introduced in commit 0aa4950d21a. The commit added `resolveRawConfiguredAcpSessionKey` as a fallback resolver for channels lacking compiled binding support. The function needed to match the established accountId semantics where an omitted accountId matches only the default account, but the author implemented simplified logic that allows omitted accountIds to match any account instead. The correct implementation already existed in `resolveAccountMatchPriority` at `src/channels/plugins/configured-binding-match.ts:17-26`, but was not consulted during the implementation of this new fallback resolver.

